div.p:
As of possible assistance to the Legation in any further consideration of the subject under reference, there is transmitted herewith a summary of treaty provisions which appear to warrant examination in connection with the question of the establishment and present status of the Rules of 1868, together with a brief discussion of the negotiations
leading to the adoption of the Rules, including pertinent excerpts from official correspondence on the subject.Correspondence consisted of despatches from the Legation in China, dated June 18, 1864, and July 2, 1868, together with certain enclosures, Foreign Relations, 1864, pt. 3, p. 426;
ibid., 1868, pt. I, p. 521.
